# Layer 6 - Presentation

## Overview

This task introduced the Presentation Layer, which is Layer 6 of the OSI Model. The Presentation Layer is responsible for data translation, formatting, and standardization between applications. It ensures that data sent from one system can be properly understood by another system, regardless of the software being used. This layer is also responsible for security functions such as data encryption.

---

